#sharelaughter #spreadsmiles

#Repost @officialhumansofbombay
‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢
‚ÄúI‚Äôd only just begun scaling the ladder in my career 6 years ago ‚Äì I‚Äôd been selected & had started filming for 2 movies. One night, after celebrating my birthday, my friend & I took a bike ride. We met with an accident which severed the artery in my right leg ‚Äì I was rushed into surgery. 
Despite 13 surgeries, my leg was infected & needed amputation. I was devastated! Dealing with it wasn‚Äôt easy, but when my family & friends supported me & didn‚Äôt look at me any different, it helped me move on.
I decided to get rid of the negativity ‚Äì I got batman crutches to remind myself of the superhero within & I began addressing my journey online. Soon, amputees & their families reached out to me. I even met some of them, to help them realise that it wasn‚Äôt the end.
I remember there was this boy who was an amputee. He saw that, despite everything, I was still pursuing all my passions, which made him do it too! He even got his crutches customised to match mine & he now actively participates in marathons!
As I got more confident, I took up travelling too. When I went to Leh on a bike ‚Äì I was told that it‚Äôd be ‚Äòimpossible‚Äô. But the moment I reached the Khardungla pass, the highest motorable pass in the world, I felt invincible!
I remember, once, I wanted to go trekking. I was again warned that it‚Äôd be risky. But I didn‚Äôt want to miss out! So with difficulty, I completed the trek! When we reached the top, the sun was shining at it‚Äôs brightest ‚Äì I‚Äôll never forget that moment. 
But through it all, I never let go of my one & only dream ‚Äì to act. After my accident, I got a role in a movie, ‚ÄòAabhaasam‚Äô, and even though it was a cameo, it was such an enriching experience! The cast & crew made me feel so comfortable. I‚Äôve started getting more offers now, and I‚Äôd even like to play a villain once. Let‚Äôs hope that happens soon!
